benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: GET /1.0/kb/accounts - Retrieve an account by external key

covered: Valid Request scenarios (TC01-TC05) cover successful retrieval with various parameter combinations
Empty Response / No data scenarios (TC06, TC17) cover not-found and empty-database cases
Query Parameters coverage across multiple combinations (externalKey, accountWithBalance, accountWithBalanceAndCBA, audit) including invalid/edge values (TC08-TC15, TC16) and extra parameters (TC16)
Authorization coverage (TC11-TC12) ensures proper 401 handling for missing/invalid tokens
Performance/load considerations (TC20-TC21) address response time under normal/peak load
gaps: Pagination handling for large datasets is not covered
Caching behavior and headers (e.g., ETag, Cache-Control) are not tested
Authorization edge-case coverage for 403 (forbidden) not explicitly tested
Internal server error scenarios (e.g., 500) beyond service dependencies are not explicitly covered
Comprehensive negative/robust input validation beyond externalKey (e.g., further malformed inputs, encoding edge cases) could be expanded
Explicit tests for repeated or rapid consecutive requests to validate rate limiting/throttling behavior
recommendations: Add tests for pagination behavior when listing many accounts to ensure correct paging and limits
Add tests asserting caching headers (ETag, Cache-Control) and potential client-side caching implications
Add a test case for 403 Forbidden to cover authorization scope violations
Add scenarios simulating internal server errors (500) and database failures directly, in addition to dependency-related faults
Expand negative input validation coverage with additional malformed/encoded inputs and boundary cases
Introduce explicit rate-limiting/throttling tests to verify behavior under rapid successive requests
